It’s been a tradition of mine to share with you  my biggest takeaways from the past year. So here it goes… below are my 5 top lessons of 2022:

1. Give to others what you want to receive. Give to others what you want to have and experience. If I want love from someone - I will give them love, instead of waiting for it. If I want kindness- I will share kindness with someone first. If I want to be invited - I will invite first, instead of waiting and wishing for someone to invite me. By giving to others - I receive as well. I have observed that everything I give comes back 10 fold. 
2. Take it easy - life is not meant to be serious. As my nephew Alex @alexrenko says in a 100 years nobody will care about what we did or did not do today. So, go for it, whatever it is you want to do. Have a good time while doing it, laugh, love, be kind and enjoy the present moment. 
3. Face your fears and say yes to life. Many people stuggle to say - No. I’m quite the opposite. I sometimes ( often times ) find myself rejecting opportunities and find excuses not to open up to new possibilities. Fear of failure? - Most certainly. Say Yes more often and watch the magic of life unfold. 🙏 
4. Put yourself first and make it consistent. it seems like such a selfish statement but in reality we can only give to others if we have something to give. Learn to make yourself a priority - nobody else can do that for you.
5. Dancing makes me happy - so dance more. As I was filling out my Best Year journal and listing my magical moments of the year - at least 5 of them were while I was dancing. Dance as much as possible - dance alone and with family and friends. Make it a regular ritual 💃🏽What are some of your biggest takeaways this year? Do share 👇🏻👇🏻

Sharing a bit of my grandma’s wisdom with you today. “ You can’t take any of it with you…” It’s something she used to say all the time and as morbid as it is- it has always reminded me to enjoy  material things in life without getting too attached to any of it. If we are honest with ourselves, we realise we don’t actually ever own anything - even our body is rented while we are alive. Nobody will care what car you had or how big your house was and how many designer bags you owned when you are gone. Most importantly none of it is coming with you when you are gone… I find this truth liberating - we can enjoy “owning” things with this awareness - knowing that it’s all temporary and without unnecessary attachment or drawing significance from the stuff we own. I’d love to hear if there is a peace of wisdom that your grandparent shared with you- please leave a comment down below and let me know what it is 👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻

If I ever find myself upset because of someone’s msg, comment, email or verbal comment - I have made it a habit now to process it before I respond. Sometimes it takes a few moments or minutes and sometimes it can take an hour or a day. Regardless- when I respond to something that triggered me - I want to first find out “ why am I triggered” “ is there a truth to it? “ “ why is this person sharing this with me? “ These are some of the questions that help me process the situation. And when I do finally respond - I always aim to respond from my heart ❤️ ( a place of love) and not my mind. ( ego) Try this next time it happens to you 😉

Ahhh, I have been there millions of time, when I catch myself wanting to fit in- modifying parts of me that are beautiful and unique in their own way. I ask myself “ why? “ - the answer is always simple. There is always this desire to belong, to be loved and accepted. Then I become aware that I can give that love and acceptance to myself - it has to come from the inside, not the outside. So, I let go and challenge myself to embrace my uniqueness and always be unapologetically ME. Because in our authenticity lies our true POWER. ❤️ Please like and share this post if it has resonated with you 👇🏻

STORY TIME - We booked a private teacher for Alexa to learn skiing today, as she has never skied before. I came to practice around while she has her lesson- I’m pretty beginner skier myself as I only learnt to ski when I was 23 and maybe skied 3-4 times in my life myself 😂. Wheh she got on skis - she froze and got terrified. The teacher really tried his best and stayed patient but after 1.5 hour of Alexa crying while she was trying to teach her we decided for him to call it a day. The whole time I stayed calm and patient with Alexa - I tried to put myself in her shoes. It can be so scary to try something new that’s unknown. I kept reassuring her that she is safe and that I totally believe she can do it. When he left - we went back on the little slope and she tried to go down a few times with me - while I held her hand. She calmed down and was finally excited to learn and then she did it all on her own 🙏 Why am I sharing this with you? This is a good example that we all have to face our fears when we start something new- sometimes the fear is irrational and can paralyse us from making a decision or taking an action. Often times - the fear wins and we play it small in life by creating a self made prison called - comfort zone. Full life, true freedom lies outside of that comfort zone. I’m so grateful I convinced Alexa today to face her fear and not give up on herself - even though it was very scary. At the end of the day when we were leaving the slopes - Alexa said she can’t wait to come back and ski again tomorrow 😃 Big win 🙏❤️ Let me know if this resonates 👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻

When it comes to making important decisions in life, it’s crucial to tune in to your inner voice and pay attention to how you feel. Your intuition is your guiding light, and it knows what’s best for you. 🌟
Always remember that your values and vision are the foundation of a fulfilling life. If something aligns with them, it should feel effortless and bring you joy. But if it causes you distress or unease, it may not be the right path for you. 🤔
So take the time to reflect on your thoughts and emotions. Ask yourself the tough questions, and be honest with yourself. Are you losing sleep over it? Does it align with your goals and purpose? 🤔
You are worthy of a life filled with positivity, joy, and purpose. Trust your instincts, stay true to yourself, and keep an open mind. The universe always has a plan, and by listening to your inner voice, you’ll find your way to it. 🌈✨

End of a Beautiful Chapter of our Lives…

We have spent the most incredible sixteen years together, being married for thirteen of them. We have dreamed and created the life of our dreams together. We are truly grateful for the love we got to experience as partners. When we got married and exchanged our vows, we never promised forever because we understood that life can take unexpected turns. Instead, we committed to giving our best every day, and that's exactly what we did for many joyful years. Our relationship wasn't perfect, but it was filled with fun, adventure, peace, romance, laughter, and authenticity. We got gifted and got to experience something all of us dream of - an incredible love story ❤️

Being best friends meant absolute honesty, and this year, we arrived at a crossroads where our paths diverged. It wasn't a decision taken lightly; we contemplated it for months but ultimately came to a decision on September 11th to give each other independence. We are grateful for the time we've shared and will continue to be great friends, co-parents to Alexa ❤️, and business partners as we navigate this new path. 

We treasure the acceptance, radical transparency, and unconditional love we have created. Regardless of what lies ahead, we choose love, kindness, and authenticity. We wish the best for one another. 

Thank you for your kindness, love, and for being a part of our journey.
With love and gratitude,
Alex and Mimi ❤️🙏

Whilst we all can find ourselves comparing our lives to others always remember that these feelings of jealously, hate and envy are not mandatory. When you have deep gratitude for what you have but you are battling through something in your professional or personal life you’ll have more empathy and understanding that others will probably going through the same too.

Someone is probably looking at your life thinking “ah they’re so lucky” “I wish I had that” but you perhaps can’t see it. So spend time in solitude, sit with yourself and recognise all of your amazing traits and qualities. I promise you, you have LOADS 💛
